Very good -- a must see for every family

Great story of a man who used to be active in the gay lifestyle and who managed to get out and even get married to an opposite sex spouse and have kids. While his message may not be a "fit" for everyone who is gay, his story is one of someone who wanted to get out and did so, with God's help.  I appreciated his insights as to how he ended up in the lifestyle and the factors that got him there. Also, a realistic portrayal of the struggles involved in trying to get out. Would have been a five star if he had been more up to date with current ministries that are still in effect for those who wish to leave the lifestyle. However, the threat of lawsuits and some folks in leadership of various ministries reverting back to their old ways have diminished the reputation of former ministries aimed at the sexually broken.
I've given this to a gay friend.  So far no comment.
I found the first half of the DVD to be very preachy. The testimonies were very good. If I could erase the first part, I would give the DVD 5 stars.
